FBIS4-24037 "drafr120_a_94005" FBIS-AFR-94-120 Daily Report 21 Jun 1994 CENTRAL AFRICA Rwanda Ambassador: Government Supports French Initiative Ambassador: Government Supports French Initiative LD2106171794 Brussels La Une Radio Network in French 1600 GMT 21 Jun 94 LD2106171794 Brussels La Une Radio Network French BFN [Excerpts] Violence is still prevailing in Rwanda. [passage omitted] As for the Rwandan interim government, which was set up at the beginning of the wave of violence in Rwanda, it has just taken sides. As was expected, this government has expressed support for the French initiative through the Rwandan ambassador in Brussels. However, Rwandan Ambassador Francois Ngarukiyintwali, first clearly denied that there were French troops in the government zone: [Begin Ngarukiyintwali recording] First, I would like to recall the allegations made by the Rwandan Patriotic Front [RPF] about the alleged presence of French troops in Rwanda. The Rwandan Government supports the initiative of the French Government in launching humanitarian intervention on the ground in Rwanda, with a view to protecting and rescuing people who are in a dangerous situation. The Rwandan Government believes that this humanitarian and [word indistinct] action should cover both the zone controlled by the government and that occupied by the RPF. [end recording]
